AhWKQSYKHUsBCXkQ6AEITjAG#v=onepage&q=one%20of%20the%20oldest%20clubs%20of%20india%20is%20in%20patna&f=false|title=Patna: A Paradise Lost!: Saga of a 2500 Year Old City from Ajatshatru to Present Day Patna|last=Sahay|first=Navneet|date=2016-11-04|publisher=Notion Press|isbn=9781946204547|language=en}}</ref> It was founded in 1865<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/bankipore-club-turns-150-old-timers-rue-its-missing-charm-115122700060_1.html|title=Bankipore Club turns 150, old-timers rue its missing charm|last=India|first=Press Trust of|date=2015-12-27|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2017-12-16}}</ref> during the [[British Raj]]. The club is located in Bankipore neighbourhood of Patna.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a-QaOP5nK-MC&pg=PA59&dq=bankipore+club&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjvsfvfhpTYAhUL1CYKHVJKD8QQ6AEIKTAA#v=onepage&q=bankipore%20club&f=false|title=Bihar And Orissa District Gazetteers Patna|last=O`malley|first=L. S. S.|date=1924|publisher=Concept Publishing Company|isbn=9788172681210|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\nThe club was founded in 1865 on the banks of river Ganges in Bankipore area of Patna. J.P.W.Johnstion was the founder secretary of the club. The club was originally known as the European Club and was used exclusively by [[Europeans]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bankiporeclub.com/about_us.html|title=::: About Bankipore Club ::: Estd. 1864|website=www.bankiporeclub.com|access-date=2017-12-18}}</ref> It was renamed Bankipore Club later, as Bankipore was the civil station of Patna District.\n\nThe club has hosted renowned personalities like cricketer [[W G Grace]] and [[Sir Edmund Hillary]]. Hillary preferred to stay at the club when he undertook a rowing expedition across the Ganges.<ref name=\"TOI\">{{Cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/bankipore-club-turns-150-old-timers-rue-its-missing-charm/1/556495.html|title=Bankipore Club turns 150, old-timers rue its missing charm|access-date=2017-12-18}}</ref>\n\n==Club Building==\n\nThe main building of the club houses the reception, lobby and offices.\n\n==Facilities==\n\nThe club facilities include a health club, [[Gym|gymnasium]] and a swimming pool.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/patna/Come-April-pools-open-for-swimming/articleshow/46971972.cms|title=Come April, pools open for swimming - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2017-12-18}}</ref> Club also has facilities such as squash, billiards and pool tables for its members. It also has a multi-cuisine restaurant and four [[Suite (hotel)|suites]] for the guests. The club also provides its grounds for marriages and various events.\n\n==Membership==\n\nThe club currently has 600 permanent members and 1500 service members.\n\n==Other facilities==\n\nThe club also has conference hall for affiliated club members. There is parking facility for guests' cars on club's premises.\n\n==In popular culture==\n\n[[E M Forster]] in his popular novel [[A Passage to India]] gave shadow reference to Bankipore Club as Chandrapore Club.<ref name=\"TOI\" />\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[List of India's gentlemen's clubs]]\n* [[New Patna Club]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Sport in Patna]]\n[[Category:Clubs and societies in India]]\n[[Category:1865 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Culture of Patna]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Patna]]\n", "name_user": "JalenFolf", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Removing link(s) to \"Europeans\":WP:OLINK. (TW))", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bankipore_Club"}
{"title_page": "Fosun International", "text_new": "{{redirect|Fosun}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = Fosun International\n| logo                = Fosun logo new.png\n| type                = [[public company|Public]]\n| traded_as           = {{SEHK|656}}\n| founder             = {{ubl|[[Guo Guangchang]]|[[Liang Xinjun]]|[[Wang Qunbin]]|[[Fan Wei (entrepreneur)|Fan Wei]]|Tan Jian}}\n| foundation          = {{ubl|{{start date|1992}} (predecessor)|{{start date|1994}} (as Fosun Hi-tech)|{{start date|2004|12|24|df=yes}} (as Fosun Intl.)}}\n| predecessor         = \n| location            = {{ubl|[[Shanghai]], China|Hong Kong (registered office)}}\n| area_served         = \n| key_people          = {{ubl|Co-Chairman: Guo Guangchang|Co-Chairman: Wang Qunbin|Co-CEO: Chen Qiyu|Co-CEO: Xu Xiaoliang}}\n| industry            = [[Conglomerate (company)|Conglomerate]]\n| products            = \n| services            = [[Investment|Diversified Investment]]s\n| revenue             = \n| operating_income    = \n| net_income          = \n| parent              = Fosun International Holdings\n| num_employees       = \n| divisions           = \n| subsid              = [[Thomas Cook Tourism]]\n| homepage            = {{url|www.fosun.com}}\n}}\n{{Chinese|title=Fosun International Limited\n|t=\u5fa9\u661f\u570b\u969b\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\n|s=\u590d\u661f\u56fd\u9645\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\n|p=F\u00f9x\u012bng Gu\u00f3j\u00ec Y\u01d2uxi\u00e0n G\u014dngs\u012b\n|order=st\n|altname=Fosun International\n|t2=\u5fa9\u661f\u570b\u969b\n|s2=\u590d\u661f\u56fd\u9645\n|p2=F\u00f9x\u012bng Gu\u00f3j\u00ec}}\n\n'''Fosun International Limited''' is a Chinese [[conglomerate (company)|conglomerate]] and investment company.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fosun-international.com/en/company/ |title=BLANK |website=www.fosun-international.com |accessdate=2008-02-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924014910/http://www.fosun-international.com/en/company/ |archivedate=24 September 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Founded in 1992 by [[Guo Guangchang]] and four others, the company is headquartered in [[Shanghai]] and was [[Incorporation (business)|incorporated]] in [[Hong Kong]] in 2004. Its Co-CEOs are [[Xu Xiaoliang]] and Chen Quiyu. [[Wang Qunbin]] joined Guo Guangchang as Co-Chairman in early 2020.<ref name=\"Bloomberg:\">{{cite web |last1=Zhao |first1=Shirley |title=Fosun Names Co-Chairman, Picks Two Presidents as Co-CEOs |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-21/fosun-names-wang-qunbin-co-chairman-two-presidents-as-co-ceos |publisher=Bloomberg |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=21 February 2020}}</ref> The company is located in 16 countries and ranked 416th on the Forbes Global 2000 ranking. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-businessreport.com/article/fosun-every-day-more-international/ |title=Fosun, every day more international |publisher=The Business Report |accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n=== 1990s ===\n'''Fosun Group''' was founded in 1992 as the Guangxin Technology Development Company by five graduates<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ejinsight.com/20170331-fosun-loses-one-more-founding-member/|title=Fosun loses one more founding member|date=2017-03-31|website=EJ Insight|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> of Fudan University in Shanghai:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fosun.com/language/en/p/3459.html|title=Life on the go for Fosun Group CEO|last=|first=|date=31 May 2012|website=Fosun|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=10 February 2020}}</ref> [[Guo Guangchang]],<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/fosun-chairman-guo-guangchang-farmers-son-with-a-streak-of-enterprise|title=Fosun chairman Guo Guangchang: Farmer's son with a streak of enterprise|last=hermes|date=2015-12-21|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> [[Liang Xinjun]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/russellflannery/2017/03/28/liang-xinjun-billionaire-co-founder-of-china-investment-firm-fosun-departs-as-ceo/|title=Liang Xinjun, Billionaire Co-Founder Of China Investment Firm Fosun, Departs As CEO|last=Flannery|first=Russell|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> [[Wang Qunbin]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/wang-qunbin/|title=Wang Qunbin|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> ({{zh|s=\u6c6a\u7fa4\u658c}}), [[Fan Wei (entrepreneur)|Fan Wei]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/fan-wei/|title=Fan Wei|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> ({{zh|s=\u8303\u4f1f}}), and Tan Jian ({{zh|s=\u8c08\u5251}}).<ref name=\":0\" />  Fosun started its business by doing market research.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.travelweekly.co.uk/articles/338134/fosun-what-you-need-to-know-about-the-chinese-conglomerate-set-to-take-a-majority-stake-in-thomas-cook|title=Fosun: What you need to know about the Chinese conglomerate set to take a majority stake in Thomas Cook|last=Taylor|first=Ian|date=19 July 2019|website=Travel Weekly|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> The major holding company of the group, Fosun Pharmaceutical Company, was incorporated in 1994 in mainland China.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|last=Zhang|first=Wenxian|url=https://books.google.co.il/books?id=At9pDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA142&lpg=PA142&dq=holding+company+fosun+high+technology+1994&source=bl&ots=4t_b_f3abt&sig=ACfU3U0n1B5fc0FUkJpdX_b0kpy3pqPvXQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiz79adzt3mAhUNUxUIHa_1DxUQ6AEwBHoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=holding%20company%20fosun%20high%20technology%201994&f=false|title=A Guide to the Top 100 Companies in China|last2=Alon|first2=Ilan|date=2010|publisher=World Scientific|isbn=978-981-4291-46-0|language=en}}</ref>  The company specialized in producing medication for [[Hepatitis A]], which occurs often in China.<ref name=\":1\" /> Then Fosun extended its business into the healthcare industry,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bhalla|first=Mohit|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/healthcare/biotech/healthcare/chinas-fosun-emerges-fourth-contender-for-cash-strapped-fortis-healthcare/articleshow/63806040.cms|title=China\u2019s Fosun emerges as the fourth contender for cash-strapped Fortis healthcare|date=2018-04-18|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> real estate,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Babar|first=Kailash|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/property-/-cstruction/fosun-invests-800-crore-in-realty-venture-with-ahuja-constructions/articleshow/71210765.cms?from=mdr|title=Fosun invests 800 crore in realty venture with Ahuja Constructions|date=2019-09-20|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://therealdeal.com/2018/10/06/what-capital-controls-this-chinese-company-is-still-buying-real-estate-overseas/|title=London Real Estate {{!}} Chinese Buyers {{!}} Fosun International|date=2018-10-06|website=The Real Deal New York|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> etc.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.wharton.upenn.edu/article/fosun-groups-guo-guangchang-marrying-chinese-momentum-global-resources/|title=Fosun Group's Guo Guangchang: Marrying Chinese Momentum to Global Resources|last=Equity|first=Private|last2=Management|first2=Strategic|website=Knowledge@Wharton|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10|last3=China}}</ref>\n\n=== 2000s ===\nIn 2004, a new holding company of the group, '''Fosun International Limited''' was incorporated in Hong Kong. In July 2007, Fosun International was listed on the main board of the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong as SEHK:656.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/74233bfe-9fa2-11e5-beba-5e33e2b79e46|title=SubChina\u2019s Warren Buffett\u2019 caught up in Beijing probe|last=Anderlini|first=Jamil|date=11 December 2015|website=www.ft.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://simplywall.st/stocks/hk/capital-goods/hkg-656/fosun-international-shares|title=Fosun International (SEHK:656) - Share price, News & Analysis|website=Simply Wall St|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n\n=== 2010s ===\nDuring 2011, the three major growth engines of Fosun, industrial profits, investment profits and asset management profits rose rapidly, enabling Fosun to make strides toward its vision of becoming \"a premium investment group with a focus on China's growth momentum\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://media.corporate-ir.net/media_files/IROL/13/130462/PPT_2011_ENG_V20_Final.pdf|title=Fosun International Limited Annual Results 2011|last=|first=|date=March 2012|website=Media.corporate-ir.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2010 through 2015, Fosun spent billions buying foreign firms in the healthcare, tourism, fashion, and banking industries in the US and Europe. These included France's [[Club Med]], Britain's [[Thomas Cook Group]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-thomas-cook-m-a-fosun-comment-idUSKBN0M20Q820150306|title=Britain's Thomas Cook soars after China's Fosun buys stake|date=2015-03-06|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-03|language=en}}</ref> Canada's [[Cirque du Soleil]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cirquedusoleil-m-a-tpg-idUSKBN0NB1AX20150420|title=Cirque du Soleil sells majority stake to U.S., Chinese investors|date=2015-04-20|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-03|language=en}}</ref> American clothing label [[St. John (clothing)|St John]], and Greek jeweler [[Folli Follie]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/news/business/21700406-chinas-leading-industrial-conglomerate-needs-shed-debt-bloated-still-bingeing|title=Bloated but still bingeing|newspaper=The Economist|issn=0013-0613|access-date=15 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=China's Fosun joins bidding war for Portuguese hospital operator|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-29321688|accessdate=23 September 2014|publisher=BBC News|date=23 September 2014}}</ref> At the end of 2014 Fosun acquired the US insurer Meadowbrook for around $433 million, marking the first full purchase of a US insurer by a Chinese company.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/12/31/us-meadowbrook-ins-m-a-fosun-intl-idUSKBN0K81MH20141231 China's Fosun to buy U.S. insurer to help finance acquisition spree]. [[Reuters]], 30 December 2014</ref> Fosun also purchased Australian oil company [[Roc Oil Company|Roc Oil]], its first acquisition in the petroleum industry.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2014/08/04/fosun-edges-out-competitor-for-australias-roc-oil/ | title=Fosun Edges Out Competitor for Australia\u2019s Roc Oil | publisher=The Wall Street Journal | date=4 August 2014 | accessdate=14 April 2017}}</ref> In 2015, Fosun acquired a controlling stake in Israeli cosmetics company [[Ahava]], despite its involvement in controversies over a plant in the [[Israeli occupation of the West Bank|Israeli-occupied West Bank]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jewishbusinessnews.com/2015/09/02/chinas-fosun-to-buy-israeli-co-ahava-for-77-million/|title=China's Fosun to buy Israeli co Ahava for $77 million|date=2015-09-02|website=Jewish Business News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 December 2015, the chairman of Fosun, [[Guo Guangchang]], was reported missing. Guo however reappeared on 14 December 2015 at a Fosun board of directors meeting. During his disappearance, Fosun requested that trading of shares be temporarily suspended.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-35068463 Chinese tycoon Guo Guangchang reported missing.], [[BBC News]], 11 December 2015. Retrieved 11 December 2015.</ref> The Fosun board of directors issued a statement saying that Guo was assisting in a government inquiry which, in their opinion, did not present a \u201cmaterial adverse impact\u201d on Fosun's finances or operations.<ref>{{Cite news|title = Another turn of the screw|url = https://www.economist.com/news/business/21684147-detention-fosuns-boss-shows-even-chinas-biggest-tycoons-are-no-longer-safe|newspaper = The Economist|access-date = 30 December 2015|issn = 0013-0613}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 July 2016, it was confirmed that Fosun had bought the English football club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] from its previous owner [[Steve Morgan (businessman)|Steve Morgan]] for an estimated \u00a345 million. Under Fosun's ownership, Wolves have progressed from being a mid table side in the [[Football League Championship]] (second tier of English football) to finishing seventh in the [[FA Premier League]], reaching an [[FA Cup]] semi-final and qualifying for European competition.<ref name=\"Fosun Group Takes Over\">{{cite news|title=Fosun Group Takes Over Wolves|url=http://www.wolves.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/news-fosun-group-takes-over-wolves-3198807.aspx|publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers|date=21 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36852323 |title=Wolves bought by Chinese conglomerate Fosun International for \u00a345m |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=21 July 2016 |accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 Fosun began to invest in India.<ref name=\"The Hindu Business Line: Fosun eyes Indian start-ups with $200-m fund\">{{cite web |last1=Pani |first1=Priyanka |title=Fosun eyes Indian start-ups with $200-m fund |url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/fosun-eyes-indian-startups-with-200m-fund/article9211995.ece |publisher=The Hindu Business Line |accessdate=24 February 2020 |date=12 October 2016}}</ref> \u201c[[Delhivery]]\u201d was one such investment made in 2017,<ref name=\"ETtech.com: Delhivery secures $30M from Fosun International\">{{cite web |last1=Gooptu |first1=Biswarup |last2=Ganguly |first2=Payal |title=Delhivery secures $30M from Fosun International |url=https://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/delhivery-secures-30m-from-fosun-international/58783413 |website=ETtech.com |accessdate=24 February 2020 |date=23 May 2017}}</ref> in addition to previous investments in [[MakeMyTrip]], India's largest online travel company and Gland Pharma. <ref>{{cite web |author1=Biswarup Gooptu |author2=Payal Ganguly |work=ET Tech |url=https://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/delhivery-secures-30m-from-fosun-international/58783413 | title=Delhivery secures $30M from Fosun International |publisher=[[The Economic Times]] |date=23 May 2017 |accessdate=23 May 2017}}</ref> Fosun is also involved in the Indian real estate market.<ref name=\"The Economic Times: Enter the Dragon: China's Fosun International plans to invest $1 billion\">{{cite web |last1=sharma |first1=Ravi Teja |title=Enter the dragon: China\u2019s Fosun International plans to invest $1 billion via realty private equity platform |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/banking/finance/enter-the-dragon-chinas-fosun-international-plans-to-invest-1-billion-via-realty-private-equity-platform/articleshow/54340153.cms |publisher=The Economic Times |accessdate=24 February 2020 |date=15 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 August 2019,  [[Thomas Cook Group]] announced that the group \"had agreed the main terms of a rescue package that will see Hong Kong\u2019s Fosun Tourism take over its tour operations and creditor banks and bondholders acquire its airline\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-thomas-cook-grp-investment-fosun/uk-holiday-firm-thomas-cook-agrees-key-terms-of-rescue-deal-idUKKCN1VI0JJ?il=0|title=Chinese poised to acquire world's oldest travel firm as Thomas Cook agrees key rescue terms|publisher=[[Reuters]] |date=28 August 2019 |accessdate=28 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn early November 2019, Fosun said it would purchase the Thomas Cook brand for \u00a311m. The company viewed itself as a \"potential saviour\" by purchasing the name.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-50267453|title=Thomas Cook brand sold to Club Med owner Fosun for \u00a311m|date=1 November 2019|publisher=BBC News|access-date=2 November 2019|quote=He said: \"The acquisition of the Thomas Cook brand will enable the group to expand its tourism business building on the extensive brand awareness of Thomas Cook and the robust growth momentum of Chinese outbound tourism.\"}}</ref>\n\n== Response to COVID-19 pandemic ==\nDuring the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic of 2020]], Fosun Pharmaceuticals partnered with German-based Turkish owned biotech firm Biopharmaceutical New Technologies, (BioNTech)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/life/science/turkish-owned-biotech-firm-signs-deal-with-chinas-fosun-us-pfizer-to-co-develop-coronavirus-vaccine|title=Turkish-owned biotech firm signs deal with China's Fosun, US' Pfizer to co-develop coronavirus vaccine|last=Reuters|first=Daily Sabah with|date=2020-03-18|website=Daily Sabah|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> to work on and distribute an experimental [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] vaccine. Once approved, Fosun will market the vaccine in China, and BioNTech will retain the rights to sell it internationally.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-biontech-fosunpharma-vaccine-collabor-idUSKBN2130O5|title=BioNTech in China alliance with Fosun over potential coronavirus vaccine|date=2020-03-16|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-21|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/271ee270-6796-11ea-800d-da70cff6e4d3|title=Fosun and BioNTech launch $135m vaccine hunt for coronavirus|last=Cookson|first=Clive|date=16 March 2020|website=www.ft.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/business/companies/article/3079847/china-will-become-more-influential-worlds-drug-market-rush|title=China\u2019s drugs sector may see \u2018explosive\u2019 growth as Covid-19 spurs research|date=2020-04-14|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\nFosun was part of an alliance of Chinese companies that donated medical supplies to 23 countries during the COVID-19 pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/russellflannery/2020/04/15/act-globally-chinas-fosun-international-guo-guangchang-on-lessons-from-covid-19-pandemic/|title=Act Globally: China's Fosun International Guo Guangchang On Lessons From COVID-19 Pandemic|last=Flannery|first=Russell|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, Fosun brought medical supplies to [[Milan]], [[Italy]], including 5,500 protective suits and 40,000 [[N95 mask|N95 respirator masks]] together with the Longfor Group and Beijing Taikiang Yicai Foundation. This donation was in addition to 5,000 masks that had been donated to Milan\u2019s municipal government earlier by Fosun.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-03/15/c_138880508.htm?from=groupmessage&isappinstalled=0|title=Chinese firms donate medical supplies to Italy - Xinhua {{!}} English.news.cn|website=www.xinhuanet.com|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n==Business Structure==\nFosun has a wide array of business activities, including investing in other firms, managing a number of [[Private equity fund|private equity funds]], and entering [[Joint venture|joint ventures]].\n\n=== Equity Investments ===\nFosun has invested in a number of businesses throughout different sectors, such as asset management, insurance, and industrial operations.\n\n==== Asset Management ====\n\n*[[IDERA]] (98.00%)<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://media.corporate-ir.net/media_files/IROL/19/194273/e-Annual%20Report%20(Eng).pdf|title=Fosun Annual Report 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[China Financial Services Holdings]] ({{SEHK|605}}, 4.9%)\n* Fosun Eurasia Capital (in Russia)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n*[[Hauck & Aufh\u00e4user]] (99.91%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Resolution Property]] (in UK)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n*[[Rio Bravo Investmentos]] (in Brazil)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.valor.com.br/financas/4652851/chinesa-fosun-confirma-compra-da-gestora-rio-bravo|title=Chinesa Fosun confirma compra da gestora Rio Bravo|date=29 July 2016|website=Valor.com.br|publisher=Valor Econ\u00f4mico|language=Portuguese|accessdate=6 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n==== Banking ====\n\n* [[Banco Comercial Portugu\u00eas]] (27.06%)<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://web3.cmvm.pt/sdi/emitentes/docs/PQ65733.pdf|title=Banco Comercial Portugu\u00eas, S.A. informs about increased qualified holding of Chiado, an affiliate of Fosun|date=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n* [[China Minsheng Bank]] (2.22%)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hkexnews.hk/listedco/listconews/SEHK/2016/0922/LTN20160922928.pdf|title=2016 Interim Report|date=22 September 2016|work=China Minsheng Bank|publisher=Hong Kong Stock Exchange|access-date=20 November 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Mybank (China)|Mybank]] (25.00%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==== Entertainment ====\n\n*[[Cirque du Soleil]] (25% via private equity funds managed by Fosun International and associated company Yuyuan Tourist Mart)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n*[[Club Med]] (90.10%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n* Studio 8 (60%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n*[[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/football/wolverhampton-wanderers-fc/2019/09/14/fosun-believed-to-be-open-to-selling-wolves-stake/|title=Fosun believed to be open to new Wolves investment|last=Edwards|first=Joe|website=www.expressandstar.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n\n==== Fashion ====\n\n* [[Ahava]] (99.46%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n* [[Caruso fashion|Caruso]] (73.90%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n* [[Folli Follie]] (10%, additional 3.89% stake held by Pramerica-Fosun China Opportunity Fund)<ref name=\":2\" />\n* [[Lanvin (company)|Lanvin]]<ref name=\":2\" />\n* [[Silver Cross (company)|Silver Cross]] (87.23%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n* [[St. John (clothing)|St John]] (70.00%)<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://global.chinadaily.com.cn/a/201802/27/WS5a94c4f4a3106e7dcc13e515.html|title=Fosun furthers efforts to tap fashion market - Chinadaily.com.cn|last=\u5b8b\u9759\u4e3d|website=global.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n* [[Tom Tailor]] (28.89%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n* [[Wolford]]<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==== Food and Drink ====\n\n* [[Sanyuan Group|Sanyuan Foods]] (20.45%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n* [[St Hubert (France)|St Hubert]] (98.12%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n* [[Tsingtao Brewery]] (17.99%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==== Industrial Operations ====\n\n*[[Cainiao]] (6.77%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Delhivery]] (6.5%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n*[[Fosun Pharmaceutical]] (37.94%)<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\"MW March 5\">{{cite web|last=Kang|first=Xiaoxiao|title=Fosun Pharma bidding $22.5 mln for U.S. Saladax|url=http://www.morningwhistle.com/html/2013/Company_Industry_0305/217415.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130326212635/http://www.morningwhistle.com/html/2013/Company_Industry_0305/217415.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=26 March 2013|publisher=Morning Whistle|accessdate=3 April 2013|date=5 March 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n*[[Gland Pharma]]<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Hainan Mining]] (51.57%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n* Fosun High Technology (100%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n*[[Roc Oil Company|Roc Oil]] (100%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Sinopharm Group]]<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Sisram Medical]]<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Zhaojin Mining]] (3.57%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n\n==== Insurance ====\n\n*[[Ameritrust Group]] (100%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Fidelidade]] (84.99%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Fosun United Health Insurance]] (20.00%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*NAGICO Insurances (through Peak Reinsurance)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinagoabroad.com/en/recent_transaction/fosun-s-unit-completes-the-acquisition-of-a-50-stake-in-caribbean-region-based-insurer-nagico|title=Fosun subsidiary completes acquisition of 50% stake in Caribbean insurer NAGICO Holdings|website=www.chinagoabroad.com|access-date=2019-05-26}}</ref>\n*[[Peak Reinsurance]] (86.93%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Pramerica Fosun Life Insurance]] (50.00%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[New China Life Insurance]] (3.28%)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2016-08/12/content_26444606.htm|title=Insurer jumps on Fosun move - Business - Chinadaily.com.cn|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n*[[United Family Healthcare]]<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Yong'an P&C Insurance]] (40.68%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==== Investment ====\n\n* Fosun Finance (86%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n* Fosun Hani Securities (100%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Miacom Diagnostics]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20140714005525/en/miacom-diagnostics-GmbH-teams-Fosun-Diagnostics-Diagnostic |title=miacom diagnostics GmbH teams up with Fosun Diagnostics, a Diagnostic Division of Shanghai Fosun Pharmaceutical Group |date=14 July 2014 |website=Business Wire}}</ref>\n*[[Guide Investimentos]] (in Brazil)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://valor.globo.com/financas/noticia/2017/09/12/chinesa-fosun-fecha-compra-de-70-da-guide-investimentos.ghtml|title=Chinesa Fosun fecha compra de 70% da Guide Investimentos|website=valor.globo.com|date=12 September 2017|publisher=Valor Econ\u00f4mico|accessdate=9 October 2019|language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\n==== Media ====\n\n* [[Focus Media]] (5.00%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==== Private Hospitals ====\n\n* Chancheng Hospital<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Esp\u00edrito Santo Sa\u00fade|Luz Sa\u00fade]] (98.79%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n*[[Starcastle Senior Living]] (50.00%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==== Real Estate ====\n\n*[[Shanghai Forte Land]] (100%)<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/fosun-shanghaiforteland-idUSTOE70J07Y20110120|title=China's Fosun to buyout Forte Land for $320 million|date=20 January 2011|work=Reuters|accessdate=2017-07-27}}</ref>\n*[[Shanghai Zendai Property]] (14.0%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n* Fosun Property Holdings (100%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n**[[126 Madison Avenue]] (New York)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newyorkyimby.com/2019/06/126-madison-avenue-tops-out-51-stories-and-756-feet-above-nomad.html|title=126 Madison Avenue, aka Madison House, Tops-Out 62 Stories and 805 Feet Above NoMad|last=Young|first=Michael|date=2019-06-04|website=New York YIMBY|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n**[[28 Liberty Street]] (New York)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n**[[73 Miller Street]] (Sydney)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mingtiandi.com/real-estate/outbound-investment/fosun-acquires-sydney-office-tower-for-93m-as-chinese-catch-aussie-fever/|title=Fosun Acquires Sydney Office Tower for $93M|date=2015-01-27|website=Mingtiandi|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n** a project in {{ill|Donggang District, Dalian|zh|\u5927\u9023\u6771\u6e2f|lt=Donggang}} (Dalian) (64%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n**Citigroup Center (Tokyo)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mingtiandi.com/real-estate/outbound-investment/fosun-buys-second-tokyo-office-tower-within-five-months/|title=China's Fosun Buys Second Tokyo Office Tower in Five Months|date=2014-12-21|website=Mingtiandi|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n**[[Lloyds Chambers]] (London)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n**[[The Bund Finance Center]] (50.00%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==== Retail ====\n\n* [[Secret Recipe (restaurant)|Secret Recipe]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fosun.com/en/news/detail.html?id=1401|title=Fosun joins hands with Secret Recipe of Malaysia|date=15 February 2014|publisher=Fosun|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160404124543/http://www.fosun.com/en/news/detail.html?id=1401|archivedate=4 April 2016|accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Yuyuan Tourist Mart]] (26.45%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" /><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==== Technology ====\n\n* [[Perfect World (company)|Perfect World]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.insidermonkey.com/blog/fosun-international-thinks-perfect-world-is-perfect-254766/|title=Fosun International Thinks Perfect World Is Perfect|website=Insider Monkey|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n* [[The Floow Limited]] (15%)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefloow.com/blog/13m-investment-for-technology-firm-the-floow.html|title=\u00a313M Investment in technology firm The Floow Limited|date=6 March 2017}}</ref>\n* [[WeDoctor]]<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n==== Tourism ====\n\n* [[Atlantis Sanya Resort]] (99.81%)<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-fosun-intl-tourism-idUSKBN1HZ08O|title=China Fosun dials up tourism push with $1.74 billion Atlantis Sanya luxury resort|date=2018-04-28|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-23|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[MakeMyTrip]] (1%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n\n===Fosun-Managed Private Equity Funds===\n\n* Carlyle-Fosun<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Fosun Capital<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Fosun RZ Capital <ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Fosun Chuanghong<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Ji'nan Financial Development Investment Fund<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Pramerica-Fosun China Opportunity Fund<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Shanghai Sunvision Binhe Equity Investment Center<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Shanghai Sunvision Xicheng Equity Investment Center<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Star Capital (Shanghai Star Equity Investment L.P.)<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Weishi Fund<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n* Zhejiang Growth Fund<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n\n===Joint Ventures===\n* Nanjing Nangang Iron and Steel United (60% share capital, 50% voting rights)<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/><ref name=\":2\" />\n** Besino Environment (100%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n**Koller (84.50%)<ref name=\":2\" />\n**[[Nanjing Iron and Steel Company]] ({{SSE|600282}}, 48.19%)<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hkexnews.hk/listedco/listconews/SEHK/2016/0428/LTN20160428889.pdf|title=2015 Annual Report|date=28 April 2016|access-date=19 November 2016|work=Fosun International|publisher=Hong Kong Stock Exchange}}</ref>\n* [[Pramerica\u2013Fosun Life Insurance]] (50%)<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n\n=== Former Equity Investments ===\n\n*[[China Huarong Asset Management]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iaireview.org/scheda_legal.php?idl=114|title=China Huarong Asset Management Co., Ltd. issues new shares for $2.4 Billion|website=www.iaireview.org|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n* [[Ironshore]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insurancejournal.com/news/national/2016/12/05/433967.htm|title=Liberty Mutual to Acquire Ironshore from China's Fosun for $3 Billion|date=2016-12-05|website=Insurance Journal|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n*[[Thomas Cook Group|Thomas Cook Group Plc]]  (5.76% via Fidelidade) - Entered Compulsory Liquidation 23 September 2019<ref name=\"FosunIntl2015AR\" />\n\n==Shareholders==\nThe major shareholder of Fosun International was a Hong Kong incorporated company Fosun Holdings,<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/> which was a wholly owned subsidiary of [[British Virgin Islands]] incorporated company Fosun International Holdings. Three founders of Fosun International, [[Guo Guangchang]], [[Liang Xinjun]] and [[Wang Qunbin]], owned 64.45%, 24.44% and 11.11% respectively in Fosun International Holdings.<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/> [[Fan Wei (entrepreneur)|Fan Wei]], another founder, withdrew his stake in Fosun International Holdings in September 2015.<ref name=FosunIntl2015AR/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.fosun.com/ Official website]\n\n{{Hang Seng China Enterprises Index}}\n\n[[Category:Companies listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Conglomerate companies of China]]\n[[Category:Civilian-run enterprises of China]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Shanghai]]\n[[Category:Chinese brands]]\n[[Category:Fosun International| ]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 1992]]\n[[Category:1992 establishments in China]]\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|Fosun}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = Fosun International\n| logo                = Fosun logo new.png\n| type                = [[public company|Public]]\n| traded_as           = {{SEHK|656}}\n| founder             = {{ubl|[[Guo Guangchang]]|[[Liang Xinjun]]|[[Wang Qunbin]]|[[Fan Wei (entrepreneur)|Fan Wei]]|Tan Jian}}\n| foundation          = {{ubl|{{start date|1992}} (predecessor)|{{start date|1994}} (as Fosun Hi-tech)|{{start date|2004|12|24|df=yes}} (as Fosun Intl.)}}\n| predecessor         = \n| location            = {{ubl|[[Shanghai]], China|Hong Kong (registered office)}}\n| area_served         = \n| key_people          = {{ubl|Co-Chairman: Guo Guangchang|Co-Chairman: Wang Qunbin|Co-CEO: Chen Qiyu|Co-CEO: Xu Xiaoliang}}\n| industry            = [[Conglomerate (company)|Conglomerate]]\n| products            = \n| services            = [[Investment|Diversified Investment]]s\n| revenue             = \n| operating_income    = \n| net_income          = \n| parent              = Fosun International Holdings\n| num_employees       = \n| divisions           = \n| subsid              = [[Thomas Cook Tourism]]\n| homepage            = {{url|www.fosun.com}}\n}}\n{{Chinese|title=Fosun International Limited\n|t=\u5fa9\u661f\u570b\u969b\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\n|s=\u590d\u661f\u56fd\u9645\u6709\u9650\u516c\u53f8\n|p=F\u00f9x\u012bng Gu\u00f3j\u00ec Y\u01d2uxi\u00e0n G\u014dngs\u012b\n|order=st\n|altname=Fosun International\n|t2=\u5fa9\u661f\u570b\u969b\n|s2=\u590d\u661f\u56fd\u9645\n|p2=F\u00f9x\u012bng Gu\u00f3j\u00ec}}\n\n'''Fosun International Limited''' is a Chinese [[conglomerate (company)|conglomerate]] and investment company.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fosun-international.com/en/company/ |title=BLANK |website=www.fosun-international.com |accessdate=2008-02-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924014910/http://www.fosun-international.com/en/company/ |archivedate=24 September 2015 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Founded in 1992 by [[Guo Guangchang]] and four others, the company is headquartered in [[Shanghai]] and was [[Incorporation (business)|incorporated]] in [[Hong Kong]] in 2004. Its Co-CEOs are [[Xu Xiaoliang]] and Chen Quiyu. [[Wang Qunbin]] joined Guo Guangchang as Co-Chairman in early 2020.<ref name=\"Bloomberg:\">{{cite web |last1=Zhao |first1=Shirley |title=Fosun Names Co-Chairman, Picks Two Presidents as Co-CEOs |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-21/fosun-names-wang-qunbin-co-chairman-two-presidents-as-co-ceos |publisher=Bloomberg |accessdate=27 February 2020 |date=21 February 2020}}</ref> The company is located in 16 countries and ranked 416th on the Forbes Global 2000 ranking. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-businessreport.com/article/fosun-every-day-more-international/ |title=Fosun, every day more international |publisher=The Business Report |accessdate=24 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n\n=== 1990s ===\n'''Fosun Group''' was founded in 1992 as the Guangxin Technology Development Company by five graduates<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ejinsight.com/20170331-fosun-loses-one-more-founding-member/|title=Fosun loses one more founding member|date=2017-03-31|website=EJ Insight|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> of Fudan University in Shanghai:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fosun.com/language/en/p/3459.html|title=Life on the go for Fosun Group CEO|last=|first=|date=31 May 2012|website=Fosun|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=10 February 2020}}</ref> [[Guo Guangchang]],<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/fosun-chairman-guo-guangchang-farmers-son-with-a-streak-of-enterprise|title=Fosun chairman Guo Guangchang: Farmer's son with a streak of enterprise|last=hermes|date=2015-12-21|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> [[Liang Xinjun]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/russellflannery/2017/03/28/liang-xinjun-billionaire-co-founder-of-china-investment-firm-fosun-departs-as-ceo/|title=Liang Xinjun, Billionaire Co-Founder Of China Investment Firm Fosun, Departs As CEO|last=Flannery|first=Russell|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> [[Wang Qunbin]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/wang-qunbin/|title=Wang Qunbin|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> ({{zh|s=\u6c6a\u7fa4\u658c}}), [[Fan Wei (entrepreneur)|Fan Wei]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/fan-wei/|title=Fan Wei|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> ({{zh|s=\u8303\u4f1f}}), and Tan Jian ({{zh|s=\u8c08\u5251}}).<ref name=\":0\" />  Fosun started its business by doing market research.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.travelweekly.co.uk/articles/338134/fosun-what-you-need-to-know-about-the-chinese-conglomerate-set-to-take-a-majority-stake-in-thomas-cook|title=Fosun: What you need to know about the Chinese conglomerate set to take a majority stake in Thomas Cook|last=Taylor|first=Ian|date=19 July 2019|website=Travel Weekly|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> The major holding company of the group, Fosun Pharmaceutical Company, was incorporated in 1994 in mainland China.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite book|last=Zhang|first=Wenxian|url=https://books.google.co.il/books?id=At9pDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA142&lpg=PA142&dq=holding+company+fosun+high+technology+1994&source=bl&ots=4t_b_f3abt&sig=ACfU3U0n1B5fc0FUkJpdX_b0kpy3pqPvXQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiz79adzt3mAhUNUxUIHa_1DxUQ6AEwBHoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=holding%20company%20fosun%20high%20technology%201994&f=false|title=A Guide to the Top 100 Companies in China|last2=Alon|first2=Ilan|date=2010|publisher=World Scientific|isbn=978-981-4291-46-0|language=en}}</ref>  The company specialized in producing medication for [[Hepatitis A]], which occurs often in China.<ref name=\":1\" /> Then Fosun extended its business into the healthcare industry,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Bhalla|first=Mohit|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/healthcare/biotech/healthcare/chinas-fosun-emerges-fourth-contender-for-cash-strapped-fortis-healthcare/articleshow/63806040.cms|title=China\u2019s Fosun emerges as the fourth contender for cash-strapped Fortis healthcare|date=2018-04-18|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> real estate,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Babar|first=Kailash|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/property-/-cstruction/fosun-invests-800-crore-in-realty-venture-with-ahuja-constructions/articleshow/71210765.cms?from=mdr|title=Fosun invests 800 crore in realty venture with Ahuja Constructions|date=2019-09-20|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://therealdeal.com/2018/10/06/what-capital-controls-this-chinese-company-is-still-buying-real-estate-overseas/|title=London Real Estate {{!}} Chinese Buyers {{!}} Fosun International|date=2018-10-06|website=The Real Deal New York|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-10}}</ref> etc.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.wharton.upenn.edu/article/fosun-groups-guo-guangchang-marrying-chinese-momentum-global-resources/|title=Fosun Group's Guo Guangchang: Marrying Chinese Momentum to Global Resources|last=Equity|first=Private|last2=Management|first2=Strategic|website=Knowledge@Wharton|language=en|access-date=2020-02-10|last3=China}}</ref>\n\n=== 2000s ===\nIn 2004, a new holding company of the group, '''Fosun International Limited''' was incorporated in Hong Kong. In July 2007, Fosun International was listed on the main board of the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong as SEHK:656.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/74233bfe-9fa2-11e5-beba-5e33e2b79e46|title=SubChina\u2019s Warren Buffett\u2019 caught up in Beijing probe|last=Anderlini|first=Jamil|date=11 December 2015|website=www.ft.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://simplywall.st/stocks/hk/capital-goods/hkg-656/fosun-international-shares|title=Fosun International (SEHK:656) - Share price, News & Analysis|website=Simply Wall St|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n\n=== 2010s ===\nDuring 2011, the three major growth engines of Fosun, industrial profits, investment profits and asset management profits rose rapidly, enabling Fosun to make strides toward its vision of becoming \"a premium investment group with a focus on China's growth momentum\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://media.corporate-ir.net/media_files/IROL/13/130462/PPT_2011_ENG_V20_Final.pdf|title=Fosun International Limited Annual Results 2011|last=|first=|date=March 2012|website=Media.corporate-ir.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=29 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nFrom 2010 through 2015, Fosun spent billions buying foreign firms in the healthcare, tourism, fashion, and banking industries in the US and Europe. These included France's [[Club Med]], Britain's [[Thomas Cook Group]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-thomas-cook-m-a-fosun-comment-idUSKBN0M20Q820150306|title=Britain's Thomas Cook soars after China's Fosun buys stake|date=2015-03-06|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-03|language=en}}</ref> Canada's [[Cirque du Soleil]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cirquedusoleil-m-a-tpg-idUSKBN0NB1AX20150420|title=Cirque du Soleil sells majority stake to U.S., Chinese investors|date=2015-04-20|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-03|language=en}}</ref> American clothing label [[St. John (clothing)|St John]], and Greek jeweler [[Folli Follie]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/news/business/21700406-chinas-leading-industrial-conglomerate-needs-shed-debt-bloated-still-bingeing|title=Bloated but still bingeing|newspaper=The Economist|issn=0013-0613|access-date=15 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=China's Fosun joins bidding war for Portuguese hospital operator|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-29321688|accessdate=23 September 2014|publisher=BBC News|date=23 September 2014}}</ref> At the end of 2014 Fosun acquired the US insurer Meadowbrook for around $433 million, marking the first full purchase of a US insurer by a Chinese company.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/12/31/us-meadowbrook-ins-m-a-fosun-intl-idUSKBN0K81MH20141231 China's Fosun to buy U.S. insurer to help finance acquisition spree]. [[Reuters]], 30 December 2014</ref> Fosun also purchased Australian oil company [[Roc Oil Company|Roc Oil]], its first acquisition in the petroleum industry.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2014/08/04/fosun-edges-out-competitor-for-australias-roc-oil/ | title=Fosun Edges Out Competitor for Australia\u2019s Roc Oil | publisher=The Wall Street Journal | date=4 August 2014 | accessdate=14 April 2017}}</ref> In 2015, Fosun acquired a controlling stake in Israeli cosmetics company [[Ahava]], despite its involvement in controversies over a plant in the [[Israeli occupation of the West Bank|Israeli-occupied West Bank]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jewishbusinessnews.com/2015/09/02/chinas-fosun-to-buy-israeli-co-ahava-for-77-million/|title=China's Fosun to buy Israeli co Ahava for $77 million|date=2015-09-02|website=Jewish Business News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-23}}</ref>\n\nOn 11 December 2015, the chairman of Fosun, [[Guo Guangchang]], was reported missing. Guo however reappeared on 14 December 2015 at a Fosun board of directors meeting. During his disappearance, Fosun requested that trading of shares be temporarily suspended.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-35068463 Chinese tycoon Guo Guangchang reported missing.], [[BBC News]], 11 December 2015. Retrieved 11 December 2015.</ref> The Fosun board of directors issued a statement saying that Guo was assisting in a government inquiry which, in their opinion, did not present a \u201cmaterial adverse impact\u201d on Fosun's finances or operations.<ref>{{Cite news|title = Another turn of the screw|url = https://www.economist.com/news/business/21684147-detention-fosuns-boss-shows-even-chinas-biggest-tycoons-are-no-longer-safe|newspaper = The Economist|access-date = 30 December 2015|issn = 0013-0613}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 July 2016, it was confirmed that Fosun had bought the English football club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] from its previous owner [[Steve Morgan (businessman)|Steve Morgan]] for an estimated \u00a345 million. Under Fosun's ownership, Wolves have progressed from being a mid table side in the [[Football League Championship]] (second tier of English football) to finishing seventh in the [[FA Premier League]], reaching an [[FA Cup]] semi-final and qualifying for European competition.<ref name=\"Fosun Group Takes Over\">{{cite news|title=Fosun Group Takes Over Wolves|url=http://www.wolves.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/news-fosun-group-takes-over-wolves-3198807.aspx|publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers|date=21 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36852323 |title=Wolves bought by Chinese conglomerate Fosun International for \u00a345m |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=21 July 2016 |accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 Fosun began to invest in India.<ref name=\"The Hindu Business Line: Fosun eyes Indian start-ups with $200-m fund\">{{cite web |last1=Pani |first1=Priyanka |title=Fosun eyes Indian start-ups with $200-m fund |url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/fosun-eyes-indian-startups-with-200m-fund/article9211995.ece |publisher=The Hindu Business Line |accessdate=24 February 2020 |date=12 October 2016}}</ref> \u201c[[Delhivery]]\u201d was one such investment made in 2017,<ref name=\"ETtech.com: Delhivery secures $30M from Fosun International\">{{cite web |last1=Gooptu |first1=Biswarup |last2=Ganguly |first2=Payal |title=Delhivery secures $30M from Fosun International |url=https://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/delhivery-secures-30m-from-fosun-international/58783413 |website=ETtech.com |accessdate=24 February 2020 |date=23 May 2017}}</ref> in addition to previous investments in [[MakeMyTrip]], India's largest online travel company and Gland Pharma. <ref>{{cite web |author1=Biswarup Gooptu |author2=Payal Ganguly |work=ET Tech |url=https://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/delhivery-secures-30m-from-fosun-international/58783413 | title=Delhivery secures $30M from Fosun International |publisher=[[The Economic Times]] |date=23 May 2017 |accessdate=23 May 2017}}</ref> Fosun is also involved in the Indian real estate market.<ref name=\"The Economic Times: Enter the Dragon: China's Fosun International plans to invest $1 billion\">{{cite web |last1=sharma |first1=Ravi Teja |title=Enter the dragon: China\u2019s Fosun International plans to invest $1 billion via realty private equity platform |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/banking/finance/enter-the-dragon-chinas-fosun-international-plans-to-invest-1-billion-via-realty-private-equity-platform/articleshow/54340153.cms |publisher=The Economic Times |accessdate=24 February 2020 |date=15 September 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 August 2019,  [[Thomas Cook Group]] announced that the group \"had agreed the main terms of a rescue package that will see Hong Kong\u2019s Fosun Tourism take over its tour operations and creditor banks and bondholders acquire its airline\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-thomas-cook-grp-investment-fosun/uk-holiday-firm-thomas-cook-agrees-key-terms-of-rescue-deal-idUKKCN1VI0JJ?il=0|title=Chinese poised to acquire world's oldest travel firm as Thomas Cook agrees key rescue terms|publisher=[[Reuters]] |date=28 August 2019 |accessdate=28 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn early November 2019, Fosun said it would purchase the Thomas Cook brand for \u00a311m. The company viewed itself as a \"potential saviour\" by purchasing the name.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-50267453|title=Thomas Cook brand sold to Club Med owner Fosun for \u00a311m|date=1 November 2019|publisher=BBC News|access-date=2 November 2019|quote=He said: \"The acquisition of the Thomas Cook brand will enable the group to expand its tourism business building on the extensive brand awareness of Thomas Cook and the robust growth momentum of Chinese outbound tourism.\"}}</ref>\n\n== Response to COVID-19 pandemic ==\nDuring the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic of 2020]], Fosun Pharmaceuticals partnered with German-based Turkish owned biotech firm Biopharmaceutical New Technologies, (BioNTech)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailysabah.com/life/science/turkish-owned-biotech-firm-signs-deal-with-chinas-fosun-us-pfizer-to-co-develop-coronavirus-vaccine|title=Turkish-owned biotech firm signs deal with China's Fosun, US' Pfizer to co-develop coronavirus vaccine|last=Reuters|first=Daily Sabah with|date=2020-03-18|website=Daily Sabah|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> to work on and distribute an experimental [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] vaccine. Once approved, Fosun will market the vaccine in China, and BioNTech will retain the rights to sell it internationally.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-biontech-fosunpharma-vaccine-collabor-idUSKBN2130O5|title=BioNTech in China alliance with Fosun over potential coronavirus vaccine|date=2020-03-16|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-04-21|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/271ee270-6796-11ea-800d-da70cff6e4d3|title=Fosun and BioNTech launch $135m vaccine hunt for coronavirus|last=Cookson|first=Clive|date=16 March 2020|website=www.ft.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/business/companies/article/3079847/china-will-become-more-influential-worlds-drug-market-rush|title=China\u2019s drugs sector may see \u2018explosive\u2019 growth as Covid-19 spurs research|date=2020-04-14|website=South China Morning Post|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\nFosun was part of an alliance of Chinese companies that donated medical supplies to 23 countries during the COVID-19 pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/russellflannery/2020/04/15/act-globally-chinas-fosun-international-guo-guangchang-on-lessons-from-covid-19-pandemic/|title=Act Globally: China's Fosun International Guo Guangchang On Lessons From COVID-19 Pandemic|last=Flannery|first=Russell|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, Fosun brought medical supplies to [[Milan]], [[Italy]], including 5,500 protective suits and 40,000 [[N95 mask|N95 respirator masks]] together with the Longfor Group and Beijing Taikiang Yicai Foundation. This donation was in addition to 5,000 masks that had been donated to Milan\u2019s municipal government earlier by Fosun.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2020-03/15/c_138880508.htm?from=groupmessage&isappinstalled=0|title=Chinese firms donate medical supplies to Italy - Xinhua {{!}} English.news.cn|website=www.xinhuanet.com|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n==Business Structure==\nFosun has a wide array of business activities, including investing in other firms, managing a number of [[Private equity fund|private equity funds]], and entering [[Joint venture|joint ventures]].\n\n=== Equity Investments ===\nFosun has invested in a number of businesses throughout different sectors, such as asset management, insurance, and industrial operations.\n\n==== Asset Management ====\n\n*[[IDERA]] (98.00%)<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://media.corporate-ir.net/media_files/IROL/19/194273/e-Annual%20Report%20(Eng).pdf|title=Fosun Annual Report 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[China Financial Services Holdings]] ({{SEHK|605}}, 4.9%)\