oard Hot 100|US]]</small><ref>{{cite web|author=Quiet Riot |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/quiet-riot-mn0000859868/awards |title=Quiet Riot - Awards |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=2012-06-23}}</ref>\n!<small>[[Mainstream Rock Tracks|Rock]]</small>\n!<small>[[Canadian Singles Chart|CAN]]</small>\n|-\n| 1975\n| \"Suicidal Show\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.POPSIKE.COM/php/../QUIET-RIOT-ultra-rare-early-days-45-record-1975-RARE-RANDY-RHODES-RECORD/150962291715.html | title=Quiet Riot's first release on Magic Wand Records | publisher=popsike.com | accessdate=27 November 2013}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| 1977\n| \"It's Not So Funny\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| 1978\n| \"Slick Black Cadillac\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 1983\n| \"[[Metal Health (song)|Bang Your Head (Metal Health)]]\" \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 31\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 37\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 48\n|-\n| \"[[Cum on Feel the Noize]]\" (US:Gold, CAN:Gold)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 5\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 7\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8\n|-\n| \"Slick Black Cadillac\" (Live) \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 32\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"| 1984\n| \"Don't Wanna Let You Go\" \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 28\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n|-\n| \"[[Mama Weer All Crazee Now]]\" \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 51\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 13\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 50\n|-\n| \"Sign of the Times\" \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 28\n| style=\"text-align: